Tweak things to build with GHC-7.x

- import liftIO from Control.Monad.Trans (from mtl), thus we can avoid
  direct dependency on transformers
- Fix imports around unsafeInterleaveIO
- Typeable needs to be explicitly derived, newer GHCs accept that fine
  too

Builds with ghc-7.0.4 ... ghc-8.8.1 on my machine

commit.message:
Raise the arities of put and newFull

Currently, this patch only handles the `Trace` scheduler,
but we probably want to do something similar elsewhere.
Compat CPP

Make NFData instances force IVar wrappers

Previously, `NFData (IVar a)` instances would just define

    rnf _ = ()

This seems really strange, since `rnf undefined` will be `()`.
Change that to

    rnf !_ = ()
Avoid an extra Trace constructor

Add MonadFix instances

Add `MonadFix` instances for the `Direct`, `Sparks`, and `Trace`
versions of `Par`.

Closes #46
